        <h2 id="examples">Real LinkedIn Creator Mode examples</h2>
        <p>Creator Mode has a measurable track record across industries. Here are patterns that repeat consistently.</p>

        <h3>SaaS founder: 2,000 to 15,000 followers in 3 months</h3>
        <p>A SaaS founder enabled Creator Mode, committed to 5 posts per week, and chose hashtags in #ProductLed, #SaaS, and #Startups. Within 90 days: followers grew from 2,000 to 15,000, posts regularly hit 10,000+ impressions, and the profile generated 5-8 weekly inbound leads from content alone. The change wasn't just the mode toggle — it was that the toggle unlocked the distribution their existing posting habit couldn't access.</p>

        <h3>Agency owner: newsletter list built faster than email</h3>
        <p>A marketing agency owner launched a LinkedIn Newsletter after enabling Creator Mode. Within 6 weeks they had 3,000 subscribers — outpacing the 2-year growth rate of their external email list. The key driver: LinkedIn automatically invited their existing connections to subscribe when the newsletter launched.</p>

        <h3>Consultant: LinkedIn Live for lead generation</h3>
        <p>A B2B consultant used LinkedIn Live (unlocked by Creator Mode) to run weekly 20-minute "office hours" sessions. Each session attracted 200-400 live viewers. The recordings were repurposed as short clips for the rest of the week. After 8 sessions, the consultant added one enterprise client directly attributable to LinkedIn Live discovery.</p>

        <h2 id="vs-related">LinkedIn Creator Mode vs LinkedIn Premium — what actually matters</h2>

